You want to generate all subsets except for empty one. There are `2^n-1` such subsets and we can match every subset to integer value in range.  
Pseudocode

    for (int i = 1; i &lt; (1&lt;&lt;n); i++){
       x = i;
       k = 0; 
       subset = [];
       while (x) {
           if (x &amp; 1)           //if k-th bit is set in x
               subset.add(A[k]);
           x &gt;&gt;= 1;         //shift right
           k++;
       }
       print subset;
     }

