Instead of `ROWNUM AS R` you can also use `ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY HIREDATE DESC) AS R` (then you don&#39;t need the `ORDER BY HIREDATE DESC`)

`ROWNUM` with `ORDER BY` may yield unexpected results, since those are generated before `ORDER BY` in the processing steps of a SELECT statement. So, prefer using `ROW_NUMBER()` function for your `UPDATE` operation ( `UPDATE` through inline view shouldn&#39;t contain an analytic function such as `ROW_NUMBER()`. As a result you cannot use your current method, but use the one below ) :

    UPDATE EMP e 
       SET e.SAL = nvl(e.SAL,0) + 
                   (
                    SELECT SAL_ADD 
                      FROM
                      ( SELECT 100 * ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY HIREDATE DESC) as SAL_ADD, 
                               T1.EMPNO 
